  "note": "Data-driven model capability + reasoning-control registry (NEXT-INSTRUCTIONS sections 5-6). Model facts live in these versioned records, NOT in source conditionals. Each record carries provenance (source URL, publisher, retrieval date). Match rules are EXPLICIT: 'exact' matches a full id; 'prefix' matches an id that starts with the pattern; 'regex' is an explicitly documented pattern. A record only asserts what its source supports; everything else stays 'unknown'. Effort/thinking values here are DEFAULTS pending a live conformance probe against the user's gateway, which overrides them.",
